  <static seed="97" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/FractionSubtractionWordProblems10.pg">
    <statement><p>A trail<rsq/>s total length is <m>{{\frac{7}{18}}}</m> of a mile. It has two legs. The first leg is <m>{{\frac{1}{6}}}</m> of a mile long. How long is the second leg?</p>
<p>The second leg is <fillin characters="11" name="AnSwEr0001"/> of a mile in length.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{2}{9}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>This is a subtraction problem.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {{\frac{7}{18}}} - {{\frac{1}{6}}} 
      \amp = \frac{7}{18}-\frac{1 \cdot 3}{6 \cdot 3} \\
      \amp = \frac{7}{18} - \frac{3}{18} \\
      \amp = \frac{7-3}{18} \\
      \amp = \frac{4}{18} \\
      \amp = {{\frac{2}{9}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>The second leg is <m>{{\frac{2}{9}}}</m> of a mile in length.</p>
</solution>
